      <subsection name="SchemaCrawler Whitepapers and Documentation">
        <p>To read more about SchemaCrawler, you can read:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            IT journalist Lee Schlesinger's blog on
            <a href="http://www.schlesinger.us/?p=650">
              SchemaCrawler
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a href="http://www.devx.com/Java/Article/32443">
              Java API Makes Database Metadata as Easily Accessible as
              POJOs
            </a>
            for an introduction to the SchemaCrawler API. (This article may
            refer to an older release
            of the
            SchemaCrawler API, but the
            concepts are the same.)
          </li>
          <li>
            The SchemaCrawler API
            <a href="apidocs/index.html">javadocs
            </a>
            .
          </li>
          <li>
          Download the
          <a href="https://sourceforge.net/projects/schemacrawler/files/SchemaCrawler%20Examples/">SchemaCrawler examples</a>
          for an overview of all SchemaCrawler features and capabilities.
          </li>
        </ul>
